This division has multiple units that provide eDiscovery litigation support, custom software development, business intelligence and data management services. Data security and disaster recovery are key to the maintenance and operations of the AGO's voice and data systems. The division also ensures compliance with state governance policies and standards, and ensures that all electronic services function properly and securely. Duties What does an IT Business Analyst - entry level position do? This position serves as an entry level IT business analyst. This position uses knowledge of the customer's business to independently provide technology related business analysis, project management, troubleshooting, IT problem resolution and technical training to Attorney General Office staff. This position enables agency staff to provide excellent legal services to protect the rights of the people of Washington State, recover revenue for the State, and disburse recovered funds to the people of Washington State. IT Business Analysis — Perform entry level industry-standard business analysis processes when planning, designing, and implementing IT systems to meet the business requirements of customers. Translate business needs into technical requirements to establish new IT systems as well as improving existing business related IT systems. Tasks include : Facilitate meetings to elicit business requirements, functional specifications and clearly write them as technical requirements for new and existing technical applications and databases. Ensure compliance with technical and stakeholder requirements. Manage requirements and deliverables. Coordinate the Application Development effort to complete projects. Develop acceptance criteria and test solutions. Develop technical support documentation. Provides business analysis, troubleshooting and support to solve highly complex business technology problems. Recommends appropriate hardware, software or processes to solve a business problem. Develop and present technology demonstrations, classroom and technology workshops to large audiences. Prioritizes and plans work activities. IT Project Management — Manages projects using standard project management techniques. Independently decides which rules, processes, resources, materials or equipment to use to accomplish the work. Tasks include: Reports to the Executive Sponsor for the project. Initiates IT projects based on input from agency business partners, business liaisons, and business analysts which includes identifying sponsors and stakeholders, defining project roles, framing the project's business case and specifying business benefits, understanding project constraints, assumptions, and exclusions, developing a solution strategy for the project, determining the project's objectives and desired outcomes, defining project scope, defining project deliverables, identifying risks and possible mitigation strategies, creating high level project estimates, and creating project charters. Plans IT projects that include developing work breakdown structures, estimating effort, staffing the project, sequencing project tasks, determining project milestones, developing project schedules, developing communication plans, developing change management plans, developing risk plans, and obtaining approvals from project sponsors and stakeholders. Establishes and monitors project scope, schedule and budget. Defines and documents the Statement of Work and specifications for procurement needs, and develops work order contracts, as necessary, to support delivery of project objectives. Prepares and executes Request for Proposals (REP) and Request for Quotes (RFQ) and evaluates responses from vendors. Creates and provides Project Status reports and communications for sponsor, stakeholders and team members. Provides change orders when changes to the project plan is required. Conducts Lessons Learned and prepare project Closeout Reports. Qualifications Option 1; Three (3) years of experience in applying International Institute of Business Analysis' "Business Analysis Body of Knowledge - BABOK" or (equivalent) best practices for business analysis; managing projects; or equivalent experience. Option 2: Associates degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or closely related field, or two (2) years full time equivalent experience Plus Two (2) years experience in applying International Institute of Business Analysis' "Business Analysis Body of Knowledge - BABOK" or (equivalent) best practices for business analysis; managing projects; or equivalent experience. Option 3: Bachelors degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or closely related field, or four (4) years full time equivalent experience PLUS One (1) year experience in applying International Institute of Business Analysis' "Business Analysis Body of Knowledge - BABOK" or (equivalent) best practices for business analysis; managing projects; or equivalent experience. The best-qualified candidates will also possess the following desired qualifications: One (1) ore more years of information systems experience in applying Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK) , or equivalent best practices for project management Project management certifications or advanced project management training Law firm work experience and an understanding of how to support the delivery of legal services Well-developed skills in Microsoft Office/Professional products including SharePoint.
